Parameter Tampering:
Here attackers tries to manipulate parameters exchanged between the client and the server to alter application behaviou in a unintended way.
This can lead to unauthorized access, privilageescalation or data manipulation.

Examples : 
GET Request         : https://example.com/balance?user=123  -> user=456
POST Request        : item=Product&price=100  -> price=10
Cookie manipulation : Set-Cookie: role=guest -> role=admin
                      X-User-Type: Regular  -> Admin

